    <h1>Transitioning from eZ Publish to eZ Platform: Feature Comparison</h=
1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <div class=3D"contentLayout2">=20
<div class=3D"columnLayout single" data-layout=3D"single">=20
<div class=3D"cell normal" data-type=3D"normal">=20
<div class=3D"innerCell">=20
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration: none;"><span class=3D"=
status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-success aui-lozenge-subtle">UPDATED TO=
 REFLECT DECEMBER 2016 1.7 RELEASE </span><br></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration: none;">Feature changes=
 from eZ Publish to eZ Platform open source and enterprise editions:</span>=
</p>
</div>=20
</div>=20
</div>=20
<div class=3D"columnLayout single" data-layout=3D"single">=20
<div class=3D"cell normal" data-type=3D"normal">=20
<div class=3D"innerCell">=20
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">eZ Publish Feature </span></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">Description</span></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">Will it be included in eZ Platform Open Source or Enterprise Editi=
on?<br></span></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">Time Frame</span></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">e-Commerce shopping cart and product datatypes</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">Ability to manage the sale of goods and other products in eZ and t=
o give end users an online cart and a check-out process</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">The feature will not be ported to the first version of eZ Platform=
, which will serve as an infrastructure for e-commerce. eZ=E2=80=99s recomm=
endation is to use <a href=3D"http://www.silversolutions.de/eng/silver-esho=
p" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">silver.e-shop</a>, a commercial=
 solution from eZ Partner <a href=3D"http://www.silversolutions.de/" class=
=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">silver.solutions</a> that is based on e=
Z Publish Platform, or to build a solution on top of eZ Platform <em>(for i=
nstance, integrating Sylius or other e-commerce related components).</em></=
span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decorat=
ion: none;">Use with silver.e-shop is available now as a side complementary=
 solution, and in the community there is attempts at integrations with Syli=
us. An integrated solution for eZ Platform based on the next version of sil=
ver.e-shop is under development.</span></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">Online Editor</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">Ability to manage some rich text fields, apply formatting, and add=
 assets such as images or existing content. Based on TinyMCE in eZ Publish.=
</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">The Rich Text Editor is being redesigned to provide a better user =
experience. It is available in</span><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-=
decoration: none;">&nbsp;</span><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decor=
ation: none;">eZ Platform. It is no longer based on TinyMCE, but is now bui=
lt on <a href=3D"http://alloyeditor.com/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"no=
follow">Alloy Editor</a>.</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">As of Febr=
uary 2016 supports basic text styling, alignment, image/content embedding, =
and migration tool from eZ Publish for the full format.</span></p><p><span =
style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Remaining features such as custom tags and tab=
ular data is currently slated for early 2017.</span></p><p><span style=3D"c=
olor: rgb(0,0,0);">After that support for inline embed/custom tags will be =
looked into.</span></p><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">&nbsp;</span><=
/p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">eZ Flow</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">Ability to manage landing pages, create custom blocks and manage f=
low of content in a block.</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">eZ Flow is being redesigned to provide a better user experience, a=
 more visual interface and to simplify the business logic. The new feature,=
 Landing Page Management, is part of Studio and therefore only available fo=
r eZ Platform Enterprise Edition users.</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decorat=
ion: none;">As of February 2016 feature parity with eZ Flow, and greatly im=
proved editorial experience.</span></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">ODT Import and export</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">Ability to import Open Office (ODT) documents (and, with an extens=
ion, Word documents) as a content object (not as a file)</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decorat=
ion: none;">This feature will not be built into eZ Platform in the short te=
rm. Import services will be developed first. </span></p><br><span style=3D"=
color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration: none;">eZ is researching similar feature=
s for online word processors such as Google Docs, since desktop software - =
especially Open Office - is losing market share </span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">No plans. It =
could come as a nice contribution to eZ Platform from the community as a Bu=
ndle.</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">Multi-upload</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decorat=
ion: none;">Ability to drop a selection of many files in one =E2=80=9Cdrag =
and drop=E2=80=9D into the content repository and have them imported as ass=
ets (File, Image, Video or others=E2=80=A6) based on the MIME type of the f=
ile.</span></p><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration: none;">=
Note: this is distinct from the ODT import in that with ODT import the file=
s are just uploaded into a Field Type such as File, Image or other.</span><=
/p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">This feature will be ported to</span><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0=
,0);text-decoration: none;">&nbsp;the Enterprise Edition as an editorial to=
ol in Studio</span><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration: none;"=
>. It will be available in the Sub-item view of a Content item to allow the=
 simple creation of image galleries, for example. It will also be available=
 from the content edit view directly to minimize the number of clicks for t=
he editor when creating collection of items. The feature is named <a href=
=3D"https://jira.ez.no/browse/EZS-894" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofol=
low">File Import</a>.</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">Target: First half of 2017. It will likely be introduced progressi=
vely.</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">WebDAV</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">Ability to navigate the content repository using a WebDAV client, =
and ability to read and write from there (ie. to create documents)</span></=
td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decorat=
ion: none;">This is not a feature that we plan to implement for eZ Platform=
 since the WebDAV protocol is used less and less and extremely unstable dep=
ending on the client software used.</span></p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0=
,0);text-decoration: none;">A potential replacement for this feature would =
be to use a CMIS client but it is equally unstable and not widely adopted.<=
/span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">No plans. It could come as a nice contribution to eZ Platform from=
 the community as a Bundle.</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">Content Staging</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">An extension that enables users to set up content workflow across =
different eZ Publish installations (for example: create content on one inst=
allation and transfer into another one at some point, for staging or archiv=
ing reasons).</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">While this eZ Publish extension has been adopted by organizations =
for several use cases, it has not always fully answered the business needs.=
 eZ plans on to bring similar capabilities to eZ Platform Enterprise Editio=
n users, but in a different way. For that, eZ will not =E2=80=9Cport=E2=80=
=9D content staging to the new platform but instead will redesign features =
and develop them progressively on the new products. Initially, eZ will deve=
lop Content Deployment services within eZ Platform and a =E2=80=9CWorkspace=
=E2=80=9D feature in the Enterprise Edition that will enable users to creat=
e content in a workspace and then deploy it to a location local or remote f=
rom the installation the user is in. This will enable editors to deploy con=
tent to environments such as Test, Production or others. The feature is cal=
led <a href=3D"https://jira.ez.no/browse/EZP-24260" class=3D"external-link"=
 rel=3D"nofollow">Workspace</a>. </span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decorat=
ion: none;">Plan is to design the deployment services sometime in 2017 and =
implement after that.</span></p><br><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-d=
ecoration: none;">In the Enterprise Edition, our plan is to have content de=
ployment capabilities in a workspace also in 2017.</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">Image Editor</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">A simple image editor which allows image manipulation such as resi=
zing, cropping, flipping, rotating and simple image effects such as blurrin=
g elements in a photo and placing a watermark.</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">eZ plans to create an image editor in the Enterprise Edition. Imag=
e editor will be slightly redesigned to be more user-friendly. A key goal, =
allowing the creation of image variations such as size and compression, may=
 be done in a second phase.</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">This is not prioritized for 2017. It could be accelerated by user =
contributions.</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">Import/Export eZPkg package system</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">eZPkg is a convenient way to import and export content, but also c=
ontent types, styles and extensions, into a single package that can be used=
 for deployment.</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decorat=
ion: none;">We are not planning to port this feature in a similar way to eZ=
 Platform. </span></p><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration: =
none;">We plan to implement the content import/export capability using a co=
ntent deployment service, which will use API directly to replicate some or =
the full amount of content from one repository to another; preferred format=
: XML or JSON.</span></p><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoratio=
n: none;">For the deployment of styles, extensions and Content Types, we ar=
e still investigating but many requests suggest to use source control for t=
hat.</span></p><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration: none;">=
Topic still to be refined.</span></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">No plan and no timing in the short term but some of the problems t=
his feature solved will be covered by other features such as content deploy=
ment in workspaces.</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">Legacy Monitoring</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">eZ Publish Enterprise customers can benefit from a service of site=
 monitoring that is used to better understand how their installation evolve=
s (i.e., size of the content repository).</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decorat=
ion: none;">The legacy site monitoring service will not be ported to the ne=
w platform. </span></p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration: no=
ne;">New monitoring, which is being designed, will focus more on monitoring=
 the installation from a software perspective (content repository, web serv=
er, database) to make sure it is healthy and conforms to the requirements o=
f the platform. The new monitoring will focus less on the activity on the p=
latform itself (ie. monitoring the object created etc.).</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">A new monitoring service is under consideration for eZ Platform En=
terprise Edition.</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">eZ Find / Advance Search</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration=
: none;">An extension that upgrades search capabilities into a strong enter=
prise search engine, thanks to the use of the Solr Open Source search softw=
are.</span></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decorat=
ion: none;">In eZ Platform, access to powerful search capabilities is now b=
uilt-in to the platform with the ability to use Solr (and, in the future, p=
robably <a href=3D"https://www.elastic.co/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"=
nofollow">Elasticsearch</a>) as a back end for the repository search and na=
vigation. No standalone extensions or bundles required.</span></p><p><span =
style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration: none;">Specifically:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style=3D"text-decoration: none;"><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);te=
xt-decoration: none;">Search capabilities in the APIs are built into eZ Pla=
tform.</span></p>
<ul>
<li style=3D"text-decoration: none;"><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);te=
xt-decoration: none;">With extensibility on Citeria, SortClauses and Facets=
 far exceeding what was possible in eZ Find.</span></p></li>
</ul></li>
<li style=3D"text-decoration: none;"><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);te=
xt-decoration: none;">Basic editorial search has been introduced in 2016.06=
 (1.4.0)</span></p></li>
<li style=3D"text-decoration: none;"><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);te=
xt-decoration: none;">Basic search in the front end will be built into the =
eZ Platform demo bundle.</span></p></li>
<li><p style=3D"text-decoration: none;"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);te=
xt-decoration: none;">Advance Solr Search engine with support for:</span></=
p>
<ul>
<li style=3D"text-decoration: none;"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Sco=
ring, &amp; </span><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">relevancy sorting</sp=
an></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Scalability &amp; database offloadin=
g for improved performance</span></li>
<li style=3D"text-decoration: none;"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Cus=
tom fields support for FieldTypes to add custom indexes</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Solr index document plugins support =
for adding additional data</span></li>
<li style=3D"text-decoration: none;"><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">=
Support for building custom Facets</span><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);t=
ext-decoration: none;"><br></span></p></li>
</ul></li>
<li style=3D"text-decoration: none;"><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);te=
xt-decoration: none;">Advanced faceted search will be built into the eZ Pla=
tform demo bundle.</span></p></li>
<li style=3D"text-decoration: none;"><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">=
Advanced editorial search querying will be built in to the Enterprise Editi=
on.</span></p></li>
</ul><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);text-decoration: none;">There are =
so far no plans for other advanced features such as:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style=3D"text-decoration: none;"><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);te=
xt-decoration: none;">Search boost rules definition form UI</span></p></li>
<li style=3D"text-decoration: none;"><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);te=
xt-decoration: none;">Crawling of external data</span></p></li>
<li style=3D"text-decoration: none;"><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);te=
xt-decoration: none;">Federated search</span></p></li>
